					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Chasersgaming wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So if I have a Sprite that's uses 9 8x8 tiles to create a boss character, I have to use the same amount of tiles for another character even though it's smaller in size let's say 4 8x8 tiles the rest is just empty tiles.<br /></div>No.<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Or do you mean if I use the 8x16 Sprite mode then every other Sprite needs to use the same<br /></div>Also no.<br /><br />If you have a sprite that's 16x24 pixels, that would be six 8x8 components ... but it's still four 8x16 components.<br /><br />If you have a sprite that's 3x3 pixels ... that's one component regardless of whether it's 8x8 or 8x16. And all of these unused bits in both versions have to be filled with transparency, so there's a lot of empty-seeming space.<br /><br />There's nothing that says the individual components have to be aligned on the grid. Skewing things sometimes can help.</div>

